{{About|the TV series|the book of the similar name|The Good Girls Revolt}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Good Girls Revolt | image = Good Girls Revolt Logo.png | genre = [[Period drama]] | creator = Dana Calvo | based_on = {{based on|''[[The Good Girls Revolt]]''|[[Lynn Povich]]}} | writer = | director = | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Genevieve Angelson]] * [[Anna Camp]] * [[Erin Darke]] * [[Hunter Parrish]] * [[Chris Diamantopoulos]] * [[Joy Bryant]] }} | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = 10 | list_episodes = #Episodes | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * Dana Calvo * Lynda Obst * Jeff Okin * Darlene Hunt }} | producer = | editor = | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = 60 minutes | company = {{Plainlist| * Lynda Obst Productions * Annabelita Films * Farm Kid * [[TriStar Television]] * [[Amazon Studios]] }} | distributor = {{Plainlist| * [[Sony Pictures Television]] * Amazon Studios }} | picture_format = | audio_format = | channel = [[Amazon Video]] | first_aired = {{Start date|2015|11|5}} | last_aired = {{End date|2016|10|28}} | website = https://www.amazon.com/Good-Girls-Revolt/dp/B017AOY4WS }}
'''''Good Girls Revolt''''' is an American [[period drama]] [[web television]] series. It is inspired by [[Lynn Povich]]'s 2013 book ''[[The Good Girls Revolt]]'' and based on real-life events. The show was released on October 28, 2016, on [[Amazon Video]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/12/good-girls-revolt-tig-notaro-seires-amazon-red-oaks-hand-of-god-1201667888/|title=Amazon Picks Up 5 New Primetime Series & 3 Kids Series, Renews ‘Red Oaks’ & ‘Hand Of God’|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=December 18, 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=June 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Schwartz|first1=Ryan|title=Transparent Season 3, High Castle Season 2, Woody Allen Comedy and Others Get Amazon Premiere Dates|url=http://tvline.com/2016/08/07/transparent-season-3-premiere-date-woody-allen-comedy-amazon/|date=August 7, 2016|work=TVLine}}</ref>
On December 2, 2016, Amazon cancelled the series after one season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/12/good-girls-revolt-canceled-no-season-2-amazon-shopped-1201863312/|title=‘Good Girls Revolt’: No Season 2 At Amazon, Will Be Shopped Elsewhere|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=December 2, 2016|accessdate=December 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/good-girls-revolt-canceled-at-amazon-will-be-shopped-952149|title='Good Girls Revolt' Canceled at Amazon; Will Be Shopped Elsewhere|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|date=December 2, 2016|accessdate=December 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/good-girls-revolt-amazon-second-season-1201932120/|title=Amazon Won’t Move Forward With ‘Good Girls Revolt’|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Brian|last=Steinberg|date=December 2, 2016|accessdate=December 2, 2016}}</ref><ref name="DEADLINE">[http://deadline.com/2017/01/good-girls-revolt-officially-dead-creator-dana-calvo-1201883602/ Deadline Hollywood, ''‘Good Girls Revolt’ Is Officially Over After Rescue Efforts Fail, Says Creator'' by Nellie Andreeva, January 11, 2017], Retrieved Jan. 11, 2017.</ref>
==Plot== The series follows a group of young female researchers at ''News of the Week'' magazine in the revolutionary times of 1969. Women in the newsroom are relegated to low-level positions. Many researchers are more talented and better educated than their male counterparts (the reporters), and do writing that the reporters incorporate directly into their stories, yet are paid less. The women have a sense that they're paid a lot less, and during the series it emerges just how much lower their pay is. But also at issue is the fact that their writing is not recognized: on the rare occasions when a female researcher's writing is openly accepted (such as when a male reporter quit just before a deadline), the story is nonetheless published under the man's name only. {{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}
==Cast== ===Main=== * [[Genevieve Angelson]] as Patricia "Patti" Robinson<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/genevieve-angelson-good-girls-revolt-amazon-pilot-cast-1201475435/|title=Genevieve Angelson Joins Amazon’s ‘Good Girls Revolt’ Pilot|first1=Dominic|last1=Patten|first2=Patrick|last2=Hipes|date=13 July 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> * [[Anna Camp]] as Jane Hollander<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/anna-camp-amazon-the-good-girls-revolt-pilot-casting-1201475287/|title=Anna Camp Joins Amazon Pilot ‘Good Girls Revolt’|first=Dominic|last=Patten|date=13 July 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> * [[Erin Darke]] as Cindy Reston * [[Hunter Parrish]] as Douglas "Doug" Rhodes * [[Chris Diamantopoulos]] as Evan Phinnaeus "Finn" Woodhouse<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/joy-bryant-chris-diamantopoulos-join-amazon-pilot-good-girls-revolt-1201478952/|title=Joy Bryant & Chris Diamantopoulos Join Amazon Pilot ‘Good Girls Revolt’|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=17 July 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> * [[Joy Bryant]] as [[Eleanor Holmes Norton]]
===Recurring=== * [[Jim Belushi]] as William "Wick" McFadden * [[Grace Gummer]] as [[Nora Ephron]] * [[Frankie Shaw]] as Naomi * Leah Machelle Cohen as Vivian * [[Daniel Eric Gold]] as Sam Rosenberg * Teddy Bergman as Gabriel "Gabe" Greenstone * [[J. P. Manoux]] as JP Crowley * [[Michael Graziadei]] as Gregory * [[Alexander DiPersia]] as Noah Benowitz * [[Cheyenne Haynes]] as Novo
