he relationships with one another and the men in their lives are redefined. |LineColor = EE714F }} }}
==Reception== ''Good Girls Revolt'' has received generally positive reviews from critics, with most comparing it to ''[[Mad Men]]'' and some calling it a female version of that show. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], a score of 71% was reported with its critical consensus saying: "''Good Girls Revolt'' features a compelling true story, told by a talented cast, even if the period drama hasn't yet achieved ''Mad Men''-level mastery".<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/good_girls_revolt/s01/</ref> On [[Metacritic]], a 66 out of 100 metascore was reported indicating, "generally favorable reviews".<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/tv/good-girls-revolt</ref>
