ith President [[Tsakhiagiin Elbegdorj]]. |- |{{flag|Tajikistan}} |[[Dushanbe]] |September 11–12 |Attended the [[Shanghai Cooperation Organisation|SCO]] summit. |- |{{Flag|Kazakhstan}} |[[Atyrau]] |September 30 | |- |{{flag|Belarus}} |[[Minsk]] |October 10 |Attended the [[Eurasian Economic Union]] Summit. |- |{{flag|Serbia}} |[[Belgrade]] |October 16 |Met with President [[Tomislav Nikolić]] and Prime Minister [[Aleksandar Vučić]]. Marked the 70th anniversary of the [[Belgrade Offensive|liberation of Belgrade]]. |- |{{flag|Italy}} |[[Milan]] |October 16–17 |Attended the 11th [[Asia–Europe Meeting|ASEM]]. Met with Prime Minister [[Matteo Renzi]], French President [[François Hollande]], German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]], Ukrainian President [[Petro Poroshenko]], European Council President [[Herman Van Rompuy]] and European Commission President [[José Manuel Barroso]]. |- |{{flag|China}} |[[Beijing]] |November 9–11 |Attended the [[APEC China 2014|APEC]] summit. |- |{{flag|Australia}} |[[Brisbane]] |November 14–16 |Attended the [[2014 G-20 Brisbane summit|G20]] summit. |- |{{flag|Turkey}} |[[Ankara]] |December 1 |State visit. Met with President [[Recep Tayyip Erdoğan]] and Prime Minister [[Ahmet Davutoğlu]]. |- |{{flag|Uzbekistan}} |[[Tashkent]] |December 10 |Met with President [[Islam Karimov]]. |- |{{flag|India}} |[[New Delhi]] |December 10–11 |Official visit. Met with Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] and President [[Pranab Mukherjee]]. |}
