====Maine==== * [[Bangor, Maine]]: A beach ball covered in Christmas lights has been thrown off the top of a local restaurant since 2005.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.bangordailynews.com/detail/133935.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120729191207/http://www.bangordailynews.com/detail/133935.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-07-29 |title=Bangor Daily News(.com): Downtown Bangor rings in 2010 |publisher=Bangor Daily News |date=2010-01-01 |accessdate=2014-05-28 }}</ref> * [[Eastport, Maine]]: A [[sardine]] is dropped in a nod to the area’s history in the herring fishing and [[canning]] industry. This is the second of two object drops in Eastport (see also "Atlantic Time Zone" above). Both objects were created by sculptor Bill Schaefer of [[East Machias]].<ref name="tidesinst"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boston.com/news/local/articles/2006/12/29/a_sardine_will_drop_in_maine/ |title=Boston(.com): A sardine will drop in Maine |publisher=Boston |date=2006-12-29 |accessdate=2014-05-28}}</ref> * [[Kennebunk, Maine]]: A wild blueberry ball has dropped from the town's First Parish Unitarian Universalist Church on Main Street since 2015.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.facebook.com/nyekbk |title=Facebook: NYEKBK |publisher=Facebook |date=2015-12-31}}</ref> * [[Machias, Maine]]: A giant plastic [[lobster]], holding a [[shovel]] and [[blueberries]] is lowered. It took place at [[Pat's Pizza]], during 2016.
