re drops candy in commemoration of the Knights Candy Store that operated there during the 1950s to 1970s.<ref name="pennlive.com"/> * [[Hummelstown, Pennsylvania]]: A [[lollipop]] is dropped.<ref name="postgazette">{{cite news|url=http://www.pittsburghpostgazette.com/pg/06361/749097-51.stm |title=City won't drop the ball on New Year's, but see what others drop |work=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |date=2012-03-17 |accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref> [http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/12/new_years_eve_celebrations_wha.html] * [[Ickesburg, Pennsylvania]]: A [[french fry]] is dropped.<ref name="perrycountytimes">{{cite news |url=http://www.perrycountytimes.com/archives/pages/2008/011008f.htm |title=Fry falls into 2008 |work=Perry County Times |year=2008 |accessdate=2012-05-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091223094804/http://www.perrycountytimes.com/archives/pages/2008/011008f.htm |archivedate=2009-12-23 |df= }}</ref>' * [[Kennett Square, Pennsylvania]]: For 2014, a steel [[mushroom]] was dropped. Kennett Square, often called "The Mushroom Capital of the World", is one of the largest growers of mushrooms.<ref name=mnn-mushroom>{{cite web|title=Pennsylvania town to celebrate new year with giant mushroom drop|url=http://www.mnn.com/lifestyle/arts-culture/stories/pennsylvania-town-to-celebrate-new-year-with-giant-mushroom-drop|work=Mother Nature Network|accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref> * [[Lancaster, Pennsylvania]]: A red [[rose]] is dropped.<ref name="postgazette"/> [[Image:LebanonBolognaDrop2008.jpg|thumb|Lebanon's 12&nbsp;ft, 150&nbsp;pound New Year's Eve bologna]] * [[Lebanon, Pennsylvania]]: A 100-pound stick of Lebanon [[Bologna]] is dropped. The bologna itself is distributed to a local [[food bank]] and [[animal shelter]] following the drop. For the 2016-2017 this has been modified to ten 20 sticks.<ref name="postgazette"/><ref name="pennlive.com"/> * [[Lewistown, Pennsylvania]]: A bag of Hartley's [[potato chips]] is dropped.<ref name="lewistown"/> * [[Lisburn, Pennsylvania]]: A pair of yellow pants or "britches" is dropped in honor of the [[Yellow Breeches Creek]].<ref name="pennlive">{{cite web|url=http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/12/new_years_eve_celebrations_wha.html |title=New Year's Eve celebrations: What's dropping where |publisher=PennLive.com |date=December 2009 |accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref><ref>[http://www.villageoflisburn.us/ Lisburn] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101106085155/http://www.villageoflisburn.us/ |date=November 6, 2010 }}</ref><ref name="pennlive.com"/> * [[Lititz, Pennsylvania]]: A [[Moravian star]] is raised.<ref name="lancasteronline"/> * [[Liverpool, Pennsylvania]]: A canal boat is dropped.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpool.pa.net/historians/postcards2003.html |title=Liverpool 2003 Postcards |date=2003-01-31 |accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref> * [[Marysville, Pennsylvania]]: A replica of the Rockville Bridge that was made my a local Cub Scout Pack is being dropped <ref name="pennlive.com"/> * [[Media, Pennsylvania]]: A ball is dropped.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://visitmediapa.com/calendar |title=Events Calendar |accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref> * [[Manheim, Pennsylvania]]: A ball is raised.<ref name="lancasteronline"/> * [[McClure, Pennsylvania]]: A kettle is dropped in honor of McClure Bean Soup Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/site/mcclure1867/ |title=Four Years All In A Day: McClure, Pennsylvania Est. 1867 |date= |accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref> * [[McVeytown, Pennsylvania]]: An ice cream cake is dropped.<ref name="usatoday2016"/> * [[Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania]]: A [[wrench]] is dropped.<ref name="pennlive1"/><ref name="cumberlink"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mechanicsburgchamber.org |title=The Mechanicsburg Chamber of Commerce |accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref><ref name="pennlive.com"/> * [[Middletown, Dauphin County, Pennsylvania|Middletown, Pennsylvania]]: A metal [[Rhombicuboctahedron]], referred to by the organizers as a "sphoctagon" (portmanteau of sphere and octagon), is dropped.<ref>[http://middletownborough.com/Matters/2005_fall/NewYearsCelebration.asp Middletown Matters Neswletter&nbsp;– Fall/Winter 2005&nbsp;– New Year’s Eve Celebration<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009012946/http://middletownborough.com/Matters/2005_fall/NewYearsCelebration.asp |date=October 9, 2007 }}</ref> * [[Myerstown, Pennsylvania]]: A tablet of [[Bayer]] [[aspirin]] has been dropped since 2013–14; Bayer operates a manufacturing plant in Myerstown.<ref>[http://www.goodwillfire.net/indexPage.php?333 Bayer Aspirin Tablet Drop] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160109235345/http://www.goodwillfire.net/indexPage.php?333 |date=2016-01-09 }} information from the 2013–14 drop. Retrieved December 29, 2014.</ref> * [[New Bloomfield, Pennsylvania]]: A [[box huckleberry]] is dropped.<ref name="wgal"/> * [[Newville, Pennsylvania]]: A big [[Spring (device)|spring]] is dropped.<ref name="cumberlink"/> * [[Palmyra, Pennsylvania]]: "The Giant Shoe" is dropped.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palmyra250.com |accessdate=December 19, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222111821/http://palmyra250.com/ |archivedate=December 22, 2010 }}</ref> * [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]]: A ball representing the planet earth, made of recycled materials, was raised for 2007.<ref name="postgazette"/> * [[Port Royal, Pennsylvania]]: A [[sprint car]] is dropped.<ref name="lewistown"/> * [[Pottsville, Pennsylvania]]: A bottle of [[D.G. Yuengling & Son|Yuengling]] [[beer]] is raised.<ref name="postgazette"/> * [[Reamstown, Pennsylvania]]: "Wobbly Bob" on a [[beer barrel]] is dropped.<ref>https://reamstownhistory.wordpress.com/special-events/</ref>[http://www.readingeagle.com/news/article/new-years-eve-events-in-and-around-berks] * [[Red Lion, York County, Pennsylvania|Red Lion, Pennsylvania]]: A wooden [[cigar]] held by a [[lion]] is raised.<ref n