{{Italic title}} '''''Midnight Son''''' is an opera by composer [[Gordon Kerry]] and librettist [[Louis Nowra]]. The contemporary opera is inspired by the true story of the murder of Melbourne woman [[Maria Korp]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/opera/midnight-son-20120517-1yt8a.html|title=Midnight Son|last=Shmith|first=Reviewed by Michael|date=2012-05-18|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/theatre/notes-from-a-lethal-love-affair-20120511-1yhny.html|title=Notes from a lethal love affair|last=Hanusiak|first=Xenia|date=2012-05-12|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|access-date=2017-05-25|language=en-US}}</ref>
''Midnight Son'' was premiered by [[Victorian Opera (Melbourne)|Victorian Opera]] in May 2012 at the [[Malthouse Theatre, Melbourne|Merlyn Theatre, CUB Malthouse]] in Melbourne.<ref>{{Citation|title=Midnight Son: an opera from tragedy|date=2012-05-12|url=http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/musicshow/midnight-son--an-opera-from-tragedy/4006282|language=en-AU|accessdate=2017-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/arts/review-midnight-son-victorian-opera/news-story/a5ad39c8e130fd03d272ad1eb8971e20?sv=46d02a2586ae17cd8e7d71ae8f5b00de|title=Midnight Son ★★★½|last=Herbert|first=Kate|date=May 17, 2012|work=|access-date=2017-05-25|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
It was nominated for [[Helpmann Award for Best New Australian Work|Best New Australian Work]] and [[Helpmann Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]] at the [[13th Helpmann Awards|2013 Helpmann Awards]].
